{"type":"article","slug":"vir/content/4/4/577","journal":"vir","canonical":"https://www.sgmjournals.org/vir/content/4/4/577","meta":{"title":"Relationship Between the Sedimentation Coefficient and Molecular Weight of Bacteriophages","authors":["Pitout, M. J.","Conradie, J. D.","van Rensburg, A. J."],"journalTitle":"Journal of General Virology","journalAbbrev":"","volume":"4","issue":"4","firstpage":"577","lastpage":"","date":"06/01/1969","doi":"10.1099/0022-1317-4-4-577","issn":[],"pmid":"5803273","mjid":"vir;4/4/577","section":"","abstractUrl":"http://vir.sgmjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/4/4/577","fulltextUrl":"","pdfUrl":"http://vir.sgmjournals.org/cgi/reprint/4/4/577.pdf","publicUrl":""},"abstractHtml":"<p>Bacteriophage PL25 was purified by centrifugation in caesium chloride. It has <i>S</i>°<sub>20,w</sub> = 485; <i>D</i>°<sub>20,w</sub> = 0.68 x 10<sup>-7</sup> cm.<sup>2</sup>/sec. and M.W. = 54.3 x 10<sup>6</sup>. An equation was derived relating <i>S</i>°<sub>20,w</sub> and molecular weight of bacteriophages.</p>","bodyHtml":"","referencesHtml":"","affiliationsHtml":"","correspHtml":"","pdfPath":null,"summaryHtml":"","ccTier":"tier3-abstract","refdomains":0}